Maybe you could fill us in a little more. For starters, what&#39;s an Astro 
Engine? What kind of intervals are you trading? What are the 
inputs/outputs going to be? What is your data set size? How are you 
going to prevent over-fitting?

1. I think it&#39;s impossible to say without knowing more.
2. Not theoretically. I suppose at some point, your net gets too slow to 
be practical.
3. The EPlex C++ framework: 
http://eplex.cs.ucf.edu/software.html#gaucij_HyperNEAT
Also, Colin Green&#39;s SharpNEAT (C#) framework: 
https://sites.google.com/site/sharpneat/

Also, are you doing this for fun or profit? If you&#39;re doing it for 
profit, there are a ton of other considerations that you have to take 
into account, particularly regarding trading costs and regulations.

Wesley

